Callionymus gardineri, the longtail dragonet, is a species of dragonet native to the western Indian Ocean.  It can be found at depths of from 30 to 180 metres (98 to 591 ft).  This species grows to a length of 28 centimetres (11 in) TL. The specific name honours the British zoologist John Stanley Gardiner (1872-1946).